# Plan Deviations

When code in this repo intentionally **does not match** what its governing implementation plan promised, the deviation is recorded in two places:

1. **A `PLAN-DEVIATION:` source-code marker** at every code site that's part of the divergence.
2. **An entry in `docs/PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md`** with full context (what the plan said, what we shipped, why, anti-instructions).

This avoids the "next agent reads the plan, sees the code doesn't match, 'fixes' it back to the plan, and silently breaks the user's actual desired behavior" failure mode.

## Before you edit code

If you grep / read a file you're about to change and find a `PLAN-DEVIATION:` marker:

1. **Stop.** Read the cited entry in `docs/PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md` first.
2. Decide whether your task works **with** the deviation (almost always) or **reverts** it (rare — confirm with the user before doing this).
3. If you keep the deviation: don't delete or weaken the marker. If your edit makes the deviation more obvious or moves it, move the marker too.

## When you're shipping a new deviation

If your change diverges from a documented plan:

1. Add an entry to `docs/PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md` (the doc's "How to record a new deviation" section has the template).
2. Add a `PLAN-DEVIATION: <id> — short reason` marker at every divergence site, citing the ID.
3. Add a brief "Update YYYY-MM-DD: see PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md#<id>" callout in the plan doc itself near the affected section. Don't delete the original plan text — the index relies on the contrast.
4. Mention the deviation in `docs/DEVELOPMENT-LOG.md` (one line + link is enough).

## Marker syntax

Match the file's comment style; keep it greppable on the literal string `PLAN-DEVIATION:`.

```ts
// PLAN-DEVIATION: 2026-04-20-cut-stacked-bands — type union narrowed; bands removed.
// See docs/PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md#2026-04-20-cut-stacked-bands for context.
```

```js
/* PLAN-DEVIATION: 2026-04-20-cross-tech-drag-end — finalizeDrag now resolves cross-tech drops.
   See docs/PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md#2026-04-20-cross-tech-drag-end. */
```

```md
<!-- PLAN-DEVIATION: 2026-04-20-cycle-chip-to-edgetab — see docs/PLAN-DEVIATIONS.md -->
```

## Vendored library exception

Changes inside `vendor/react-native-resource-calendar/` use the existing `// FORK Phase N` markers as their primary tag, and `vendor/react-native-resource-calendar/README-FORK.md` is their primary index. Add a `PLAN-DEVIATION:` marker **on top of** a `FORK Phase` marker only when that phase reverses or contradicts a separate implementation plan (not just adds a feature). Both can coexist on the same code.

## Don't

- Don't use `PLAN-DEVIATION:` for ordinary refactors, bug fixes that match the plan, or cosmetic changes. The marker is for "we are intentionally NOT doing what the plan said."
- Don't reuse an ID. IDs are stable forever, even after a deviation is reverted (reverts get their own ID and the old entry moves to "Resolved / superseded").
- Don't skip the index entry just because the inline comment is detailed. The whole point is that an agent or teammate reading any one of the touched files can find the others via the index.
